kbones, and all of them interconnect at various NAPs around the world.\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-01-20 03:59:56'),(340,'#cluster #intro','set of connected computers that work together so that they can be viewed as a single system',NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 22:55:26'),(341,'#ff #firefox #addons #ads #AdblockEdge','addon_name:  Adblock Edge\nfork of the Adblock Plus version\nprovide the same features as Adblock Plus 2.X \n  created by Wladimir Palant',NULL,NULL,'2015-01-15 05:57:37'),(342,'#youtube #yt #ff #firefox #addons #ads #flash#dl','addon_name:  Flash and Video Download\nDownload Flash and videos with a single click',NULL,NULL,'2015-01-15 05:56:30'),(343,'#ip #ff #firefox #addons #ip#domain #info#gathering #reconnaissance','addon_name:  IP Address and Domain Information\nThe Ultimate online investigation tool! See detailed information about every IP Address, Domain Name and Provider.\n************\nIf You use the NoScript Add-on or other JavaScript blocking add-on, please add www.tcpiputils.com to the Whitelist. If you don\'t see the icon you can use the hotkey CTRL-SHIFT-I to show the popup.***************\nThis extension displays detailed information about the current website. The information can be used for online investigation and SEO purposes.',NULL,NULL,'2015-01-15 06:02:48'),(344,'#ip #ff #firefox #addons #proxy #geo#location','addon_name: Proxy Finder (IP Switcher)\nChange your Geo-location with one click\na Firefox extension which automatically switches an Internet connection across one or more proxy servers. Put simply, Proxy Finder automates the manual process of editing Firefox\'s Proxy Settings dialog. Proxy server switching occurs based on the Manual or Automatic mode you define.\nIn the manual mode (default) you need to choose a protocol (http, https, socks4, or socks5) and enter a desired IP and Port, then press ON/OFF button to start the proxy. For the automatic mode, the extension uses its online server to search for a working proxy based on the protocol(s) and origin you have chosen.\n\nMoreover, animated icons show you when a proxy is in use. Advanced logging shows you which proxies were used. If you have any question or concern, feel free to contact me via the following address: philip[dot]tholus[at]gmail.com\n last_updated: 15/01/2015',NULL,NULL,'2015-01-15 06:09:23'),(345,'#ip #ff #firefox #addons #vimperator','addon_name: vimperator\nVimperator adds an efficient, Vim-inspired user interface on top of Firefox\n    last_updated: 14/01/2015',NULL,NULL,'2015-01-15 06:11:41'),(346,'#mysql #change#prompt',NULL,NULL,'\nusing my.cnf\n	vi ~/.my.cnf\n		[mysql]\n		prompt=\\u@\\h [\\d]>\\_\n\nfrom mysql\n	mysql> prompt u@h [d]>\n\nfrom bash\n	export MYSQL_PS1=\"u@h [d]> \"\n\ngeneric variables:\n==============================================================\n\\ displays single quote\n\\v displays server version\n\\p displays port\n\\n displays newline\n\\d displays default database\n\\u displays username\n\\U displays username@hostname accountname\n\nfor more information:\n	http://www.thegeekstuff.com/2010/02/mysql_ps1-6-examples-to-make-your-mysql-prompt-like-angelina-jolie/\n','2015-01-15 06:58:07'),(347,'#mysql #comment#table #create#table',NULL,NULL,'create table table00(\n...\ncol00 text;\n...\n) comment \'this is the comment for this table\'\n','2015-01-15 09:15:02'),(348,'#mysql #comment#column #alter#table',NULL,NULL,'\nalter table table00 comment \'this is the new comment\';\n','2015-01-15 09:15:02'),(349,'#mysql only#field#name of#db00',NULL,NULL,'select COLUMN_NAME from information_schema.COLUMNS where TABLE_NAME=\'db00\';','2015-01-16 09:18:54'),(350,'#mysql only#field#type#name of#db00',NULL,NULL,'select COLUMN_NAME,COLUMN_TYPE from information_schema.COLUMNS where TABLE_NAME=\'db00\';','2015-01-16 09:20:07'),(351,'#mysql #manage #db','db(information_schema) is a db which has all information about the db in the server\n  information_schema.columns contains information about columns, etc....... ',NULL,NULL,'2