rcycle or bicycle.\n    What matters is the hardware and software used in the test\n    \'\n    the following is the schematic of the std_connections:\n\n                                                                +-----------+\n                                                                |  scanner  |\n                                                                +----+------+\n                                        +----+                       |\n                         +-----+        | pc |                       |\n                         | gps +--------+----+-----------------------+\n                         +-----+       /    /            +--------+\n                                      ------+--+     +---| dongle |\n                                               |     |   +--------+\n                                               +-----+\n                                                     |\n                                                     |    +--+\n                                                     +----|ms|\n                                                          +--+ \n\nthe pc will output sth like the follows;\n    \n              |           |\n              |<--Road--->|       +----  ms   : signal level - best server --+\n              |           |       |                ........                  |\n              |           |       |                                          +-- output file\n         +----+       +---+       +---- gps   : latitude - longitude         |\n         |            |           |                .........                 |      of\n         |    +-+     |           |                                          |\n         |    |x+-----------------+----- scanner : other servers             |    the pc\n         |    +-+     |                            .........               --+\n         |            |\n   ------+     +------+\n               |\n               |\n   ------------+\nGPS: collecting the data of latitude and longitude of each point\n    and more things, but those are the most important\n\'\nms: mobile data collections, such as signal strength,\n    best_server\n\'\nscanner:    collecting data throughout the network\n\nCurrently, there are already cell phones that do everything.\n    They have a GPS,\n    collection of specific software\n    \'\n    but they are very expensive\n\nSTEPS:\n    The routes are predefined in the office\n        it indicates where testing will occur.\n        \'\n        This area is defined based on several factors, mainly related to the purpose of the test.\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-02-28 15:41:02'),(869,'#gsm -main-signalling-channels','\nhttp://www.whytelecom.com/content/signaling-channel-gsm-radio-interface\nbch\n    transmitted by the bts to the ms\n    it carries sys_param\n    bcch\n    fcch\n    sch\n    cbch\ncch\nsdcch\nacch\nccch\n\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-02-28 17:12:26'),(870,'#gen_c #lakh','\nA lakh or lac\nabbr L\na unit in the Indian Numbering System\nequal to one hundred thousand \n\n1L = 10^5\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-01 05:41:13'),(871,'#gen_c #sq.km -unit','\n1sq.km = 1km^2\n\n1sq.km = 0.3861 square miles\n         247.1 acres\n\n1 acre = about 0.004047km2, 0.4047ha or 4047 m^2\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-01 05:47:24'),(872,'create windows_bootable from linux','\nhttp://www.webupd8.org/2010/10/create-bootable-windows-7-usb-drive.html\n================================================================================\n\nmake sure that those next packages are installed:\n    gparted\n    ntfs-3g\n\nplug ur usb_stick\nopen gparted(Applications > Sys_tools > Administr > gparted)\nselect the usb_stick\n    (gparted > devices > /ur/usb_stick)\numount the usb_stick (from gparted)\nto format the usb_stick in ntfs_format\n    (partition > format > ntfs)\nmake the usb_will be bootable\n    right_click usb_stick\n    select Manage_flags > \"boot\"\nmount back the usb_drive\nsome users told that w7 installation fails\n    dl unetbootin version4