;\n\n\ninitialisation tableau\n    int tableau[4] = {85, 0, 64, 40};\n    //                0   1   2   3     :   index\n    \'\n    ou bien utiliser la boucle for\n\n\npour avoir la taille du tableau(tab00)\nint tab00[] = {\n        1, 4, 6\n    };\nint a = sizeof(tab00)/sizeof(tab00[0]);\n            ^^^^^         ^^^\n            |||||          |\n            |||||          +----- u divide it by the size of the array element.\n            |||||\n            +++++----- determine size of array in bytes\n    // a = 3\n\npour faire une tableau de taille dynamique\n    de int:\n        au lieu de:\n            int amis[] = int[nombreDAmis];\n        on fait:\n            int *amis = malloc(nombreDAmis * sizeof(int));\n    de double\n        int *amis = malloc(nombreDAmis * sizeof(int));\n','2015-03-08 23:19:32'),(945,'#c_pr -string -intro -long-list',NULL,NULL,'it is better that if u want to do manipulation of str in c\n    then load \n        #include <string.h>\nstring en c est un tableau de char\n\nchar str[] = \"salut\";\n    sa representation en memo est:\n    \'\n     addr        |       val        +-- tt str en c se \n   --------------+---------------   |     termine par\n     18000       |       s       +--+     ce char (\\0)\n     18001       |       a       |\n     18002       |       l       |\n     18003       |       u       |\n     18004       |       t       |\n     18005       |       \\0   <-+\n\n\n\n\n\n\nhere are some functions which u can use for managing the string\n========================================\nsuppose that \n    char[] txt=\"this is a test\";\n\nto get the length\n    int length = strlen(txt);\n\nto concat 2str\n    char chaine1[100] = \"Salut \", \n    chaine2[] = \"Mateo21\";\n    \'\n    strcat(chaine1, chaine2);\n    // chaine1 = Salut Mateo21\n\nto build a str01 from another str00\n    char chaine[100];\n    int age = 99;\n    sprintf(chaine, \"Tu as %d ans !\", age);\n    // chaine = Tu as 99 ans\n\n\nto copy a string\n    char